const title = "Signature Kitchen Suite Appliance Repair Los Angeles — Same Day";
const description = "Signature Kitchen Suite refrigerator, range & dishwasher repair in LA. Same-day service, OEM parts. $89 diagnostic, waived with repair.";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "What Signature Kitchen Suite appliances do you repair in Los Angeles?",
    a: "The full SKS US lineup. Integrated column refrigerators and freezers (SKSCJ3606S, SKSCF3601P, SKSCV3601P), pro dual-fuel ranges with sous vide and steam oven integration (SKSDR480SS 48-inch, SKSDR360GS 36-inch), induction cooktops (SKSCV30K and similar widths), built-in wall ovens (SKSCV2402S double, SKSCV3001P single), dishwashers (SKSDW2402P standard tub, SKSDW2401P top-control variants), range hoods matching the range collection. SKS launched in 2017 as LG Electronics' pro-luxury offshoot — positioned above LG standard appliances and competing directly with GE Monogram, Thermador, and Bosch Benchmark. We see them most often in Hancock Park, Los Feliz, and West Hollywood full-kitchen renovations where the owner wanted integrated column refrigeration at Monogram quality plus the LG smart platform for connected control."
  },
  {
    q: "How much does SKS repair cost in LA?",
    a: "Diagnostic is $89, applied toward the repair when you approve the work. SKS pricing sits in the upper-mid luxury tier — lower than Sub-Zero or Wolf, comparable to GE Monogram and Thermador on equivalent components. Common SKS service items: <strong>refrigerator side</strong> — ice maker module (the 2018-2022 column fridge pattern, see year-pattern below) $285-$485, compressor service $585-$885, evaporator fan motor $245-$385, condenser fan motor $245-$385, defrost timer $185-$285, InstaView panel connectivity board $385-$580, water inlet valve $185-$285. <strong>Range side</strong> — ceramic igniter $185-$285 per zone, spark module $245-$385, oven thermostat $265-$405, convection fan motor $325-$485, bake / broil element $245-$385, control board $345-$525, sous vide circulator pump $385-$580 (Pro Range integrated sous vide is a brand-specific component). <strong>Dishwasher side</strong> — drain pump $245-$385, water inlet valve $185-$285, control board $345-$525, door latch $185-$285. SKS parts ship through the LG US network — same 2-5 day typical lead as LG standard appliances, which is the best parts availability among the luxury brands we service. Faster than Monogram (Louisville KY, 2-5 day), notably faster than Italian-origin or German brands."
  },
  {
    q: "How does Signature Kitchen Suite compare to GE Monogram?",
    a: "Honest comparison from servicing both regularly: SKS and Monogram occupy the same price tier and compete for the same Hancock Park, Los Feliz, Pasadena upper-tier kitchen renovations. <strong>SKS</strong> is built on the LG Electronics platform (LG launched the pro-luxury brand in 2017), runs LG's smart platform with InstaView door-in-door technology and connected app integration, parts ship through LG's well-developed US distribution network (same 2-5 day lead as LG standard). Pro Dual-fuel ranges include integrated sous vide circulator and steam oven cavity, which Monogram doesn't offer. <strong>Monogram</strong> is built on the GE Appliances platform (GE Monogram has been around since 1986, currently Haier-owned), runs the SmartHQ connected platform, parts ship through GE Appliances US distribution from Louisville KY (also 2-5 day lead). Mature dealer network, well-established factory service. Build quality is comparable across the two — both 18-22 year service life targets, both stainless construction with similar component-level specifications. SKS has the edge on smart-platform integration (the LG ecosystem is more developed than GE's SmartHQ). Monogram has the edge on dealer-network depth and parts ecosystem maturity. Repair costs run comparable in the standard wear-item band; SKS smart-platform components (InstaView, sous vide circulator) carry brand-specific parts that don't have direct Monogram equivalents."
  },
  {
    q: "Can you repair the LG InstaView panel on my SKS refrigerator?",
    a: "Yes. InstaView is the door-in-door knock-to-see technology on SKS column refrigerators (and on some LG standard refrigerators) — knock twice on the glass panel and the interior lights up so you can see what's inside without opening the door. The technology runs through a sensor module behind the glass plus a control board that handles the knock-detection algorithm and the lighting trigger. Common InstaView failures: <strong>knock-detection stops working</strong> (sensor module fault, $285-$405 with labor, OEM LG part); <strong>interior light not triggering on knock</strong> (control board issue, $385-$580); <strong>panel display showing wrong status or connectivity errors</strong> (board + WiFi module replacement, $385-$580); <strong>glass panel itself damaged</strong> (panel replacement $585-$985, requires careful coordination because the glass is laminated with the touch-sensor layer). The 2018-2022 SKS column refrigerator cohort specifically shows InstaView panel connectivity issues around year 3 to 4 — the same timeline as the ice maker module pattern (see year-pattern callout). When both show up matched-cycle, we diagnose and quote both together. InstaView repairs are common LG-network parts, typical 2-5 day arrival when not stocked on the truck."
  },
  {
    q: "How fast can you get SKS parts?",
    a: "Among the best parts availability in the luxury tier. SKS parts ship through the LG Electronics US distribution network — the same supply chain that handles LG standard appliances — and that network is one of the best-developed parts pipelines in the residential appliance business. Typical lead time: 2-5 business days for most components. Common wear items (ice maker modules, water inlet valves, ceramic igniters, drain pumps, control boards) often available next-day or same-day from regional LG distribution. Brand-specific SKS components (Pro Range sous vide circulator, InstaView panel and control board) typically 3-5 days. This is significantly faster than Sub-Zero (5-10 days from Madison WI), comparable to GE Monogram (Louisville KY 2-5 days), and dramatically faster than Italian or German brands (ILVE 14-21 days, Gaggenau 5-10 days). The LG parts-availability advantage is a real consideration when comparing SKS against other luxury brands for a kitchen renovation — service downtime is shorter."
  },
  {
    q: "How long do SKS appliances last?",
    a: "SKS appliances are designed for 18-22 year service life — comparable to GE Monogram and Thermador, slightly below Sub-Zero / Wolf's 25-30 year targets but within the same general luxury-tier durability band. The components that wear are predictable: ice maker module year 3-4 on the 2018-2022 column fridge cohort specifically (see year-pattern callout, $285-$485), InstaView panel connectivity year 3-4 same cohort ($385-$580), compressor year 10-15 ($585-$885), convection fan motor year 8-12 ($325-$485), oven thermostat year 7-10 ($265-$405), dishwasher drain pump year 6-9 ($245-$385). Heavy-use households compress these windows by 2-3 years; lighter-use households extend by 2-4 years. Replacement-unit pricing: SKS column refrigerator 36-inch starts around $9,500, integrated column freezer 30-inch around $8,500, Pro Dual-fuel 48-inch range around $11,500, full SKS kitchen suite typically runs $35,000-$55,000 installed. Against those numbers, $400-$700 mid-life repairs on individual appliances are clearly favorable economics — the suite is designed to be serviced and maintained, not replaced as a unit. The smart-platform electronics are the newest variable in long-term service planning; first-generation 2017-2018 SKS boards are entering year-8 cycles now."
  },
  {
    q: "Where can I find the official Signature Kitchen Suite manual or warranty information?",
    a: `Our technicians work independently of SKS / LG's factory service network — we're often faster and available same-day across Southern California.`
  }
];

