        <h3>SKS SKSDR480SS 48-inch Pro Dual-fuel range, Los Feliz</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Sous vide circulator not maintaining target temperature — water heated to 130°F but couldn't hold 145°F target for low-and-slow cooking. Standard gas burners and oven worked normally.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Sous vide circulator pump running but with reduced flow rate — bearing wear at year 5 in a household that used the sous vide function multiple times weekly. Temperature sensor and integrated thermostat measured within spec.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Sous vide circulator pump replacement with OEM SKS part (LG-network 4-day arrival). Verified target temperature hold across the sous vide operating range.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost & time:</strong> $525 total. Two visits — diagnostic + parts arrival.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>SKS SKSDW2402P dishwasher, West Hollywood</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Dishwasher running full cycles but dishes coming out unwashed at the top rack. Bottom rack cleaning normally. Unit was 5 years old.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Upper spray arm assembly partially clogged plus circulation pump impeller worn. The clog explained the immediate symptom; the pump wear was the underlying year-5 service item that had reduced pressure to the upper arm.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Cleared spray arm, replaced circulation pump impeller with OEM SKS / LG part (same-day, on truck). Ran verification cycle confirming full cleaning across both racks.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost & time:</strong> $345 total. Same-day, completed on diagnostic visit.</p>
